		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Well if you don't know much about building computers, you may get in over your head. Of course there is only one way to learn and that is to do it. <br>  <br> I got started working on PC's by trying to build my own with no knowledge.. now I work as a network technician <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/1.gif" border="0" alt="happy" hspace="0" vspace="0">  <br>  <br> Although I hate to reccomend a Dell, no one can touch their prices right now. You could get a decent gaming PC for around $500, maybe $600. <br>  <br> Just make sure you pay to have ram upgrade to at least 512megs, more if it's feasible. Dell likes to sell XP machines with 128 ram and that should be illegal <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/4.gif" border="0" alt="grin" hspace="0" vspace="0"> 
