		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				CPU <br> CPU heatsink/fan <br> Motherboard <br> Memory <br> Sound card <br> Video card <br> Case  <br> Powersupply <br> Hard drive <br> CD/DVD drive/burner <br> Floppy drive <br> Ethernet card <br>  <br> Those are the parts you need. Keeping this under $500 could be difficult, especially since you want a good gaming system. <br>  <br> What I would do with your budget is get a Dell Poweredge 400SC. They go on sale every month for under $300. It uses the latest Intel 875 chipset which has all the latest and greatest features. The only thing you need to do is replace the ECC ram it comes with, with 2 512mb sticks of PC3700 ram and throw in a video card. I recommend the ATI Radeon 9600XT. <br> I got one that I use for a fileserver. Comes with a 2.4ghz Pentium 4, 800mhz fsb, hyperthreading, 80gb 7200rpm hard drive. Nice and stable. <br>  <br> Keep on eye on www.slickdeals.net and www.gotapex.com for these sales.
