				Build your own! <br>  <br> Its not rocket science. You can buy a video or a book explaining how to do it. All the pieces snap together like legos. <br>  <br> I priced out a system recently at newegg.... <br>  <br> 2.8C P4 (usually can be overclocked to 3.2Ghz+) <br> ASUS 865PE Chipset Motherboard  <br> 80 Gig HD <br> R-W DVD drive <br> R-W CD rom drive <br> 1 Gig DDR 3200 RAM (Kingston) <br> ANTEC SOHO File Server Tower ATX Case with 400W Power Supply <br> eVGA nVIDIA GeForce FX5900SE <br>  <br> And all this for about $900 which Dell could not touch! <br>  <br> Keep in mind that this stuff is almost top of the line components and you could go way cheaper than this when deciding on your system. <br>  <br> This is a top of the line gaming rig which would last for years, and unlike many dell systems, its totally upgradable. and does not come pre-loaded with Gigs of crap which you never use. <br>  <br> Plus you will have the hands-on experience of building your own computer making future builds/upgrades totally easyer. <br>  <br> For under $500 you would probably have to go with a AMD chipset and processor. I would personnaly opt for a P4 system though, spend the extra $200 and get the P4 system. <br>  <br> 		

			</td>
		</tr>
