			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				You are not going to build a system from scratch for $500. You might upgrade a system for that. <br>  <br> Even if you can get all the parts for $500 (Not likely) the OS is going to be a killer unless you have one. I highly suggest not multiinstalling an OS. A new install of a MS OS will come in for aproxamately $300. <br>  <br> Anyway, beyond all that even if money was not an issue you will pay more to build a gameing rig then buy one and by no means EVER buy a prefab unit if you want decent gameing performance. Custome machines from places like Falcon Northwest or Voodoo computers are the only way to go. Personaly I suggest a Falcon. Alien is no longer a true custom builder and there machines fall well short of Falcons and Voodoos. My 2 year old Falcon smokes brand new Aliens. <br>  <br> You can speck out a vary nice mach V from Falcon for alot less then you would think but it will definately be over $500. <br>  <br> I would expect any gameing rig worth it's salt will cost no less then $1,500 minimum no matter home built or custome. <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> 
