		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Ok. <br>  <br> You have plenty of places to buy parts from so I will give you some clues on some ways to &quot;get by&quot; for less $$ <br>  <br> I've never bought a PC before .. well except for the VIC20 but thats another story. <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/3.gif" border="0" alt="wink" hspace="0" vspace="0">  If you are going for cheap you need to get priorities straight. <br>  <br> Get a decent MB and processor. Athlons are cheaper than Intels and work great. You don't need the latest and greatest of either. An athlon 2100+ will do the job nicely and cost far less than the top of the line. Remember your on a $500 budget. <br>  <br> Get 512DDR Ram. Don't compromise on this ... 512 is the min to play anything these days and 1G is on the way to becomming standard. MMORPG's suck up the RAM so splurge on this. DO NOT buy it in 1 stick! That way if you have RAM problems you can take one out at a time to troubleshoot it. <br>  <br> Sounds cards ... WHO CARES?? Get a cheap SB16 PCI card. They are OK for gaming and while they may not have positional sound it will get you in game. If you want want killer sound be prepared to spend more than $500 <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/3.gif" border="0" alt="wink" hspace="0" vspace="0">  <br>  <br> Vid cards are going cheap these days. Everyone will tell you to get the biggest and the badest ... but if your on a budget then let them pay for it! <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/1.gif" border="0" alt="happy" hspace="0" vspace="0">  You can get inot a &quot;workable&quot; Vid card with DX9 standards for &lt; $120. It won't be the best but it will work. <br>  <br> Make sure your power supply is at least 300W. Bigger is better but 300W is the min. Vid cards suck the juice so feed them well. <br>  <br> The rest you should have. You should be able to do all of this for under $500. If you have more to spend then balance the cost of a CPU upgrade with the Vid card upgrade and don't forget the power of RAM in a MMORPG. <br>  <br> As a side note, go with Win2K. WinXP is so bloated, it will eat most of your 512RAm for lunch just booting. Its stable and its has FAR FAR better performance than XP. I know ... people say XP is the latest and greatest and designed for games .. but thats a bunch of BS. Its just another MS bloatware product. If you know anyone who can handle it, have them unlaod XP and load up Win2K. Watch how much thier performance improves. Its major. As far as gaming, I have no problems with it ever. It runs games great ... all of them. <br>  <br> Good luck! <br> 
						<p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span>
						<div class="SignatureText">
						SWG and UO are worlds that people are <br> meant to live in. AC1 and EQ are games <br> that people are meant to level in. <br> Don't confuse the two. <br> 
						</div>
							

