				<a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=879595">Post History</a> 
				 				 
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA">
			<td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%">
			<a href="/user.asp?usr=468528" class="AuthorLink">Xynteiri</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=http://media.ign.com/boardimages/star2.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="294 posts"></a><br> 
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			<span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 294<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Oct 01<br>
			</span>
			
			
			
			</td>
			
			
			<td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span> 
			3/4 10:31pm 
			<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: Building a computer
				- <span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Edited:</span> 3/4 10:43pm (2 edits total) 
				<span style="font-weight: bold;">Edited By:</span> 
				<a href="/user.asp?usr=468528" class="AuthorLink">Xynteiri</a>			
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Building you own isn't difficult. I was scared to try it for a long time then finally I did. Just don't get creative and do things by the numbers.  <br>  <br> It is much easier than you might think. <br>  <br> I will say one thing, it's amusing when people buy 500 dollar video cards but get a crappy mother board and low to average CPU. Get a good mobo, CPU, and ram. <br>  <br> I have an Abit Ic7-g  and love it to death, 8oomhz FSB with a P4 2.8c. I will be updating my ram in the future it's currently corsair 3200/400ddr. Go ahead and get a gig of ram. <br>  <br> Right now two decently priced video cards that perform well and can overclock are the Ati radeon 9800pro, and the Nvidia 5900. Some people are opting for the XT version of the 5900 because it can be overclocked to perfomance levels near the 5900ultra. Especially the Leadtek which often sports the 2.2 ram. <br>  <br> Anywho good luck .		

			</td>
		</tr>
